recentTweets.text:
The Salgado family deserves answers.

There are still many alarming questions that remain unanswered. My colleagues from Houston to Capitol Hill are standing together, and we will continue fighting for transparency and accountability for our community.

@HispanicCaucus https://t.co/UP92uIiXWQ

From Houston to Capitol Hill, we are united and we are not backing down. We will not let ICE bury the facts and deny Lorenzo Salgado Araujo’s family the truth and accountability they deserve.

ICE out. 

@HouseDemocrats

Lorenzo Salgado Araujo was a person. He was loved. He was part of our Houston community.

His family deserves the truth, and our community deserves answers. We need a real, independent investigation now.

@HispanicCaucus @LULAC @FIELHouston https://t.co/h2JFwfe2qM

Happy Independence Day! 🇺🇸

As we celebrate the 250th anniversary of our nation’s founding, we reflect on the ideals of freedom, equality, and opportunity that continue to guide us forward. #America250

@HouseDemocrats https://t.co/VmW4xx7f1Q

This week, the Supreme Court issued two rulings that put immigrant communities in danger.

We need to pass my American Dream and Promise Act to protect TPS holders. #TPS holders are our neighbors, friends, coworkers, and community members, and I stand with them.

